COMPANIES ARE rushing to fill new niches for would-be parents: in vitro fertilisation extras, swish egg-harvesting “studios” and apps to track reproductive health. But some companies promise more than science can deliver. The worrying flare-up of piracy off west Africa presents new challenges and unmitigated risks to sailors. And, lessons learned from a shooting simulator for police. Runtime: 21 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn